headline: GNRC Q2 Deep Dive: Data Center Opportunity, Energy Solutions, and Margin Outlook
summary: Power generation products company Generac (NYSE:GNRC) reported revenue ahead of Wall Street’s expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 6.3% year on year to $1.06 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.65 per share was 24.6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: The Top 5 Analyst Questions From Generac’s Q2 Earnings Call
summary: Generac’s second quarter results were met with a notably positive market reaction, reflecting management’s emphasis on commercial and industrial (C&I) product sales and demand for residential energy storage systems. CEO Aaron Jagdfeld highlighted strong shipments to industrial distributors and robust sales of residential energy technology as core drivers.
